parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel tank leaks and cracks can cause fuel to spill onto the ground, creating a fire hazard and potentially leading to accidents or injuries. The strong fumes can also make drivers feel sick and disoriented.
symptoms: Fuel leaks from the tank when it's full or nearly full
fuel leaks from the left-hand side of the tank
fuel tank cracks near the top
strong fuel fumes enter the vehicle
fuel smell is annoying and persistent.
